Class RoleUnresolvedList

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<Object>
java.util.AbstractList<Object>
java.util.ArrayList<Object>
javax.management.relation.RoleUnresolvedList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<Object>, Collection<Object>, List<Object>, RandomAccess, SequencedCollection<Object>
public class RoleUnresolvedList extends ArrayList<Object>
A RoleUnresolvedList represents a list of RoleUnresolved objects, representing roles not retrieved from a relation due to a problem encountered when trying to access (read or write) the roles.

It is not permitted to add objects to a RoleUnresolvedList that are not instances of RoleUnresolved. This will produce an IllegalArgumentException when calling methods in this class, or when using listIterator and add or set.

Since:
1.5
